			<p> Yummy!  I could eat a bowl of that right now!  I like the Raos sauces but haven&#8217;t tried the pasta. Was it worth the extra expense?</p>
<p>Like you, I prefer pasta without meat. It can just be so overwhelmingly rich when you add meat. In fact, my favourite (and now semi-famous) lasagna is meatless but very satisfying. Like you I add larger bits of cheese that emulsify the sauce the same way meat fat would so that taste is very satisfying.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s link in case you&#8217;re interested:  <a href="http://danamccauley.wordpress.com/2008/11/12/lovin-my-oven/">http://danamccauley.wordpress.com/2008/11/12/lovin-my-oven/</a></p>
